er\nmorphologies, i.e. Rood--Sastry and Bautz--Morgan types, and only a weak\nsignificant correlation with cluster richness. We find that mass has a slight,\nbut significant, tendency to increase faster than the luminosity does, M\nproportional to L_{B_j}^{1.2--1.3}. We verify the robustness of this relation\nagainst a number of possible systematics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 Jul 1999 15:22:38 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
